gomodel:SYNGO_1402  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: null mutant neurons for doc2a/b have 50-80% lower spontaneous release, which can be rescued by acute expression of doc2b. Experimental description: M&M: Doc2 DK mice\n\n2/9/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed Doc2b protein was of rat species: \"For overexpression of full length rat Doc2b neurons were infected 8-15 h prior to analysis with Semliki particles encoding full length rat Doc2b an.....\"\n- I saw no reason to prefer rat (overexpressed protein) over mouse species (DKO animal). Mouse was selected." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1402" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
